/*!
    \class Calculator
    \brief The Calculator class provides basic arithmetic operations.

    This class demonstrates \b {QDoc markup} with various commands.
    Use \c {Calculator::add()} to add numbers.
*/

/*!
    \fn int Calculator::add(int a, int b)
    \brief Adds two integers together.

    The parameters \a a and \a b are added and the result is returned.

    \sa multiply(), subtract()
*/

/*!
    \property Calculator::precision
    \brief This property holds the calculation precision.
*/

/*!
    \qmltype Button
    \brief A clickable button component.

    The Button is a \uicontrol {UI control} that responds to clicks.
*/

/*!
    \page overview.html
    \title Calculator Overview

    This is a standalone documentation page.
*/

/*!
    \fn void Calculator::configure()
    \brief Configures the calculator with default settings.

    Follow these steps to configure the calculator:

    \list 1
    \li Call reset() to clear any previous state.
    \li Set the precision using the precision property.
    \li Enable logging if you need diagnostic output.
    \endlist

    The configuration takes effect immediately after the last step.
*/

/*!
    \fn double Calculator::convert(double value, QString from, QString to)
    \brief Converts a value between two units.

    The following conversions are supported:

    \table 80%
    \header \li From \li To \li Factor
    \row \li meters \li feet \li 3.281
    \row \li {2,1} kg/pounds \li 2.205
    \endtable

    Returns the converted value, or -1 on error.
*/

